			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=1977#M1977">76</a> of 113
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 854 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
Shadowfrost wrote:<BR>
<DIV>Toofpick, you forgot to list enough things that I can tell your cleric isn't your main.&nbsp; FYI clerics also use emeralds, shrink potions/devices, and star rubies.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I'm curious about the amazing fishscale-carrying necro.&nbsp; If a necro wants to breathe underwater, they generally use DMF.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I would think that your warrior's probably&nbsp;your main,&nbsp;although you haven't listed his incarnadine bp/cobalt greaves and you seem to have far too many arrow parts:&nbsp; I recommend investing in one of those arrow-making wossnames that drop in easy LDoNs.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<DIV>Ya, I know the fishscales are pushin it <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-wink.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> I was lookin thru my bags on my Necro. The only time you need those are in an underwater&nbsp;zone where you can't cast DMF (or recast, like kedge) and don't have an EB item handy. I think I've had the same stack for the last two years, but it's one more slot tied up by&nbsp;a consumable reagent. </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warriors have it easier if they can afford cobalt legs (I wish), and the Bloody Ancille pouches are handy -&nbsp;trade the 80 arrow parts (1 stack of each part, 4 parts per combine)&nbsp;for a couple stacks of purified crystals.&nbsp;In my case, I prefer the longer range fletched arrows over the summoned arrows from the pouch.</DIV>
<P>And you're right, my Cleric isn't my main (more like MainB, he goes everywhere the other three toons I listed go). I knew I didnt have a few reagents listed&nbsp;there&nbsp;- I'll get DI someday, I swear -&nbsp;but the major complaint here seems to be the peridots. My point was that other classes have to carry around bags 'o components&nbsp;too. I see people here alluding that only clerics have to lug around bags of expendible junk like this. Sure it's annoying, but it's not worth the seething hatred I see coming out of some of the posts here.</P>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
