<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&message.id=1978#M1978">77</a> of 113
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 850 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV><BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>

<DIV>The point of clerics not wanting 9 is because our self buffs add hundreds of hps at the higher end where you group with people that are actually capable of casting 9.&nbsp; Arguing the lower levels that go pok farming has nothing whatsoever to do with class balance.</DIV>
<DIV>_____________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you can group with people that cast 9 you can group with people that cast focus.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>The point of non-high mana burning classes wanting ac is damage avoidance/mitigation.&nbsp; 40odd ac vs 100 hps? no contest.</DIV>
<DIV>Tell me, what point is there in 9 to a bard or monk?</DIV>
<DIV>______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>WoG stacks with 9 last I checked and provides a higher net AC I do believe</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>_______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>You're right, raids arent really an issue...but then neither is burning a stack of dots for a 65.</DIV>
<DIV>The only people that really get hurt by the dot costs is the low level clerics 44-55 mainly.&nbsp; That's also the range wherein you wont find enchanters having AA's for free runes.&nbsp; You snipe at my including raids and then you ignore the little guys entirely, well done.</DIV>
<DIV>______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>You'll also find that given a semi-decent tank a chanter will go through less peridots in those groups than a cleric will.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>Just for your viewing pleasure i went and checked the cost of dots and pearls.&nbsp; Rounded off the the nearest gp, dots are 10.5pp and pearls are 4.7.&nbsp;&nbsp; You must be doing some kinda funky math, cause 1/10 of 10.5 should be about 1pp no?</DIV>
<DIV>______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I didn't check the prices on this and the only reason I quoted it was because you got picky with Shadow on not quoting your whole post. I will state however the number of peridots used per raid (sorry CotH isn't exactly a commonly used group spell) is significantly high than the number of pearls used.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>_______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>The issue that's actually worth debating isnt whether clerics need to have dots removed but whether or not all such pp sinks should be removed, as they all have a similar sort of impact on players in the low-mid levels.</DIV>
<DIV>_______________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Obviously a large percentage of clerics feel this topic is quite debatable in the solo class form otherwise there would be significantly fewer posts.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>_______________________________________________________________________________________________________________</DIV>
<DIV>My personal opinion is Id like to do without, but to me it makes sense to have em.&nbsp; It's not necessarily the 'right' opinion, but it's mine.&nbsp;&nbsp; Yours would appear to be that it doesnt matter what happens to the others, as long as clerics get a discount.</DIV><BR>
<HR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; My question is how does it make sense that enchanters/shaman stop using reagents and we don't? How does it make sense that druids have no components at all? What part exactly makes sense to you? </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>As a final note, saying the peridot costs doesn't hurt 65th level clerics is stilted at best.From 60-65 + multiple AA the money you would save on peridots could go a long way to helping you upgrade you gear. At least 75% of players are NOT raiding players they have to camp/buy upgrades. I particularly enjoy the "you should ask for money or peridots" comments, it is OBVIOUSLY well balanced and fair that clerics are the only class where that would be a constant concern. I mean Plainly HP buffs that are a boon to everyone that gets them should come with this costs unlike the componentless buffs of our fellows.</P>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							You have a sword, I have a click stick, you'd have to kill me a good 20 times for every one time I kill you, now go get me a beer before we find out whether or not you can hang with that Ratio.
							</div>
								
