		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Ok , lets make something clear, if I refused to cast virtue or symbol on a group, the abuse I would get. So these spells are not optional any more. That was the justification of the cost the spell was optional you didn't require it except on raids.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wizards with spellshield, well when they have to cast it on everyone in the group all the time, it becomes a required buff, but atm its an optional buff thereby cost is justified. Enchanters with runes, again same as the wizards. I can't actually remember when I had spellshield or rune cast on me. Necro's peridot cost on pets should be removed or have an AA like mages to allow it not to be used.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Faith is the direct equivalent of nine, nine has more hps plus mana regen. WOG stacks with both, and symbol also stacks with both. The only class that doesn't use nine/symbol combo is paladin due toi a self buff that doesn't stack, which means vitue+ AotC is more hps than nine symbol for them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>As a 65 raiding cleric the costs are not severe but for an unguilded and/or lower level cleric the costs are so severe I never had more than 2K plat in the bank due to having to constantly buy dots. I had to sell equipment to be able to just buy the cheapest horse possible.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So if a buff is required it should not have a reagent cost attached, but if the buff is an optional buff yes it should have a cost attached.So hps buffs have cost removed but DI still has the cost of 2 emeralds. CoH is a tool mainly used in raiding and to save time, therefore cost stays, rune is the same.</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Caean Silverhand
							</div>
								
