			>
			<br><blockquote><hr>Laurri wrote:<br><DIV>To recap, the original intent was to point out 2 things....1:symbol is actually unique in that it stacks with absolutely everything, and therefore has _some_  justification in being charged for.   2: we're not the only ones with heavlily used expensive stuff, and if we were to get off the hook, so should the remainder....not just some, but all of them.</div><br><hr></blockquote><br><br><br>Following this line of thought, it could be argued that Blessing of Aegolism and Hand of Virtue (and possibly Hand of Conviction as well if the peridot requirement reamins) should have no reagent requirement since they DON'T stack with everything (9's). This could then be extended to include the druid 9 series to have a reagent requirement because it adds mana regeneration that stack with every other mana regeneration in the game. At the same time it can be argued that 9's shouldn't have reagent requirements because they don't stack with all HP buffs.<br><br>What I am trying to say, is that using the stacking properties of any spell as justification for reagent requirements is no valid. If it was, then more spells should have reagent requirements, that currently don't.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
